mana than it costs to make the Mystical Rod and also the old Mod Rod.  Mages have no mana regen again... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub47.ezboard.com/umakikobonestorm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Makiko Bonestorm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#330000>(10/10/02 11:59:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub47.ezboard.com/fblackburrowstoutco13800frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=86.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re:Hard Core changes on next patch</span><hr size=1> Makes sense, Gnip?  We'll see.  That will depend on what they're trying to fix and how they do it, IMO.  <br>
<br>
By VI's own admission, the &quot;problem&quot; of high monk defense stems from all of the insanely good high AC/+stats 0.0wt <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> ALL/ALL</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> or even <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> monk only</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> equipment that <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> VI has been putting in high level zones</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> since the Velius expansion.  And SoL AA monk abilities are mostly defensive.<br>
<br>
Now a couple years or so later we're told monks are &quot;too defensive&quot;? Okay, some probably are, but what total percentage of players in the game wear gear like that in the first place?  It's very small, and fewer are monks.  I don't think most monks are so overpowered as to make a MAJOR nerf necessary, so I'm waiting to see what really happens before blowing a fuse <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I'd say Mak is pretty well geared considering I bought whatever I didn't loot, and didn't have to farm much to get it.  I'm in acrylia reinforced/spider fur atm except for the RotLC and a meditative blanket I looted in TT.  I can tell you I don't make a great tank in most situations, certainly not as well as a pally or SK.  Gnip, you and I seem to take about the same beatings when a mob gets off the real tank and onto one of us...as long as you watch for those damage shields <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Yeah, I soloed 49 and 50, and from what I understand a rogue wouldn't be able to.  But the spawns I was on were 50/50 light blue and lites would beat me a quarter of the time.  Darks did it more often.  I don't think that's outrageous.  If chain-wearing melee class can't solo light blues or just-barely-darks, then maybe that class is <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> underpowered</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> in defense.  I don't think it's asking too much for a melee class to be able to solo mobs 11 lvls below you at 50.  60 yeah, but 50?<br>
<br>
As I see it, leather armor + avoidance should rougly equal chain armor, but certainly not plate.  And I think it does, roughly - maybe not exactly, but it seems close enough that if the change affects ALL monks as HARD as folks are making it sound, it will be a good ol' fashioned fuckup, not a fix.  <br>
<br>
If the problem is Oobah Monks threatening the jobs of Oobah Tanks - and they only can up to a certain point - then the response should be to either reclassify the awsome loots to count monks out (and I guess give tanks the was-Monk Only stuff, like the 60ac +10Str/Sta/Agi/Dex +100hp 0.0wt legs from Kael etc) or to lower the AC softcap for monks.<br>
<br>
As it is a monk and a warrior, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> both at the AC softcap</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, are not equal in XP group situations, because the monk dodges/ripostes more hits than the tank making the monk's EFFECTIVE ac greater than the warrrior's, and less damage = better tank.  But it apparently doesn't matter against bad-arsed NToV mobs or the like, 66+, since they usually hit for close to full damage regardless of AC.  Of course, they're the ones who drop the trouble loot in the first place.<br>
<br>
And nobody can tell me I could tank as well as a tank while playing in, say, Paludal at 20, or SD at late 40.  I tried, and it hurt a lot and wasted a lot of mana.<br>
<br>
As long as VI nerfs the soft cap only and doesn't make AC more important against high end mobs in the future, I see no problem.  I'll just be glad I don't have 30 AA points in defensive abilities.<br>
<br>
If VI nerfs all monks, or later makes AC more important for pre-PoP high end mobs, folks will be right to be throwing the fits they currently are.  Unless new Oobah monk gear is all HP and resists instead of AC, of course.  I'd be okay with that. <br>
